PRACTICAL-5 
Hosting a Web Page on EC2 (Amazon Linux 2) 
 
To set up an Apache web server on an Amazon EC2 instance running Amazon Linux 2, upload 
an HTML page, and access it via the browser. 

Step 1:Create Instance -> Give name , Select Amazon Linux 

Step2:Go to security ->Security groups inbound 
Click Edit inbound rules. 
Add a new rule: 
Type: HTTP 
Port: 80 
Source: Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0) ‚Üí or restrict to your IP. 
Click Save rules.

for safe side add https and http anywhere

Step3:Connect to Instance console

1.  
Write the commands to perform: 
sudo yum update -y 
sudo yum install httpd -y 
sudo systemctl start httpd 
sudo systemctl enable httpd 
   
Navigate to Apache‚Äôs web root: 
‚óè  cd /var/www/html 
Create or edit index.html: 
‚óè  sudo nano index.html 
1.     Add Your HTML Page 
1.     Add Your HTML Page 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Minimal Toggle</title>
    <style>
        /* Base Styles (Light Mode) */
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 30px;
            background-color: #fff;
            color: #333;
            transition: 0.5s;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Dark Mode Activation using :target */
        body:target {
            background-color: #111;
            color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        
        /* Links and General Text */
        a {
            color: inherit; /* Links inherit body color */
            margin: 0 10px;
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 5px 10px;
            border: 1px solid currentColor; /* Uses the current text color */
            border-radius: 3px;
            display: inline-block;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body id="light"> 

    <h1>Minimal Design</h1>
    
    <p>
        This page is simple, short, and uses almost no CSS. The unique feature is the **pure CSS dark mode toggle** below.
    </p>

    <div class="controls">
        <a href="#dark">Dark Mode üåë</a>
        <a href="#light">Light Mode ‚òÄÔ∏è</a>
    </div>
    
</body>
</html>
ctrl+O -> Enter (to save) 
Ctrl+x (to exit) 

